-- Argentina to Receive $400 Million in Loans From Development Bank
-- B y   R i c h a r d   J a r v i e
-- 2012-07-03T16:20:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/argentina-to-receive-400-million-in-loans-from-development-bank.html
Argentina  will receive $400 million
in loans from the Development Bank of Latin America to finance
water, sewage and highway works, the Planning Ministry said
today in an e-mailed statement.  The bank was formerly known as the Andean Development
Corporation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Jarvie in Buenos Aires at 
 rjarvie@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  